{"lc": 1, "type": "constructor", "id": ["langchain", "schema", "document", "Document"], "kwargs": {"metadata": {"doc_id": "8fd625943f36cff6043156da18f6cb3e", "source": "NexaCorp Policy Handbook v5.2", "part": "2. Code of Business Conduct & Ethics", "section": "2.4 Insider Trading & Securities Policy", "subsection": "2.4.1 Scope & Definition", "raw_content": "NexaCorp's securities policy applies to all employees, officers, directors, and contractors who in the course of their work may come into possession of material non-public information (MNPI) about NexaCorp or any publicly traded company with which NexaCorp has a business relationship. MNPI is any information that (a) has not been publicly disclosed through official channels, and (b) a reasonable investor would consider important in deciding whether to buy, sell, or hold securities.", "type": "text"}, "page_content": "Part: 2. Code of Business Conduct & Ethics\n            Section: 2.4 Insider Trading & Securities Policy\n            Subsection: 2.4.1 Scope & Definition\n            NexaCorp's securities policy applies to all employees, officers, directors, and contractors who in the course of their work may come into possession of material non-public information (MNPI) about NexaCorp or any publicly traded company with which NexaCorp has a business relationship. MNPI is any information that (a) has not been publicly disclosed through official channels, and (b) a reasonable investor would consider important in deciding whether to buy, sell, or hold securities.", "type": "Document"}}